
<h1>Basketball Court Finder</h1>
<section id="search-bar">
  <p>Enter a court name or New York City area zipcode in the search field to find basketball courts near you.
    <br> Remember just a bit of the address? you can search by that too.</p>
  <p>Zip Codes of New York City<br>
    New York City is a very large city with many ZIP codes. ZIP codes of New York City Neighborhood are listed below:<br>
    Manhattan:10001-10282<br>
    Staten Island :10301-10314<br>
    Bronx: 10451-10475<br>
    Queens:11004-11109, 11351-11697<br>
    Brooklyn:11201-11256
</p>
  <p>Entering a zip code will show you courts within a 10 mile radius of that zipcode. </p>
  <div class="search-bar">
    <form id="searchForm">
      <label class="button_text" for="searchField">Search Courts: </label>
      <input type="text" id="searchField" name="searchTerm" placeholder="Type a court name or new york city area zipcode to search for." required>
      <button class="button" type="submit">Search</button>
    </form>
  </div>

{{!-- Link to all the courts --}}
<div class="allCourts">
<p>Having trouble searching for basketball-courts? You can look through the directory of courts to find courts</p>
<a id="allCourts" href="http://localhost:3000/courts/allCourts">Directory of Courts</a>
</div>
</section>
<div class="basketball-courts">
  <h2>Trending Pick Up Games</h2>
  <p>Exciting games happening today</p>
  {{#each trendingGameList}}
    <div class="trending-game">
      <a href="game/gameDetails/{{this._id}}">
        <h4>{{this.courtName}}</h4>
      </a>
      <p>{{this.location}} - {{this.date}} - {{this.time}}</p>
    </div>
  {{/each}}
</div>

<script>
  const searchForm = document.getElementById('searchForm');
  searchForm.addEventListener('submit', (event) => {
    event.preventDefault(); 

    const searchField = document.getElementById('searchField');
    const searchText = searchField.value.trim();
    window.location.href = `http://localhost:3000/search/${searchText}`;
  });
</script>





